26#include <sys/cdefs.h>
27__KERNEL_RCSID(0, "$NetBSD: nouveau_nvkm_engine_disp_rootnv04.c,v 1.2 2018/08/27 04:58:31 riastradh Exp $");
28
29#define nv04_disp_root(p) container_of((p), struct nv04_disp_root, object)
30#include "priv.h"
31
32#include <core/client.h>
33
34#include <nvif/class.h>
35#include <nvif/unpack.h>
36
37struct nv04_disp_root {
38 struct nvkm_object object;
39 struct nvkm_disp *disp;
40};
41
42static int
43nv04_disp_scanoutpos(struct nv04_disp_root *root,
44 void *data, u32 size, int head)
45{
46 struct nvkm_device *device = root->disp->engine.subdev.device;
47 struct nvkm_object *object = &root->object;
48 const u32 hoff = head * 0x2000;
49 union {
50 struct nv04_disp_scanoutpos_v0 v0;
51 } *args = data;
52 u32 line;
53 int ret;
54
55 nvif_ioctl(object, "disp scanoutpos size %d\n", size);
56 if (nvif_unpack(args->v0, 0, 0, false)) {
57 nvif_ioctl(object, "disp scanoutpos vers %d\n",
58 args->v0.version);
59 args->v0.vblanks = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x680800 + hoff) & 0xffff;
60 args->v0.vtotal = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x680804 + hoff) & 0xffff;
61 args->v0.vblanke = args->v0.vtotal - 1;
62
63 args->v0.hblanks = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x680820 + hoff) & 0xffff;
64 args->v0.htotal = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x680824 + hoff) & 0xffff;
65 args->v0.hblanke = args->v0.htotal - 1;
66
67 /*
68 * If output is vga instead of digital then vtotal/htotal is
69 * invalid so we have to give up and trigger the timestamping
70 * fallback in the drm core.
71 */
72 if (!args->v0.vtotal || !args->v0.htotal)
73 return -ENOTSUPP;
74
75 args->v0.time[0] = ktime_to_ns(ktime_get());
76 line = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x600868 + hoff);
77 args->v0.time[1] = ktime_to_ns(ktime_get());
78 args->v0.hline = (line & 0xffff0000) >> 16;
79 args->v0.vline = (line & 0x0000ffff);
80 } else
81 return ret;
82
83 return 0;
84}
85
86static int
87nv04_disp_mthd(struct nvkm_object *object, u32 mthd, void *data, u32 size)
88{
89 struct nv04_disp_root *root = nv04_disp_root(object);
90 union {
91 struct nv04_disp_mthd_v0 v0;
92 } *args = data;
93 int head, ret;
94
95 nvif_ioctl(object, "disp mthd size %d\n", size);
96 if (nvif_unpack(args->v0, 0, 0, true)) {
97 nvif_ioctl(object, "disp mthd vers %d mthd %02x head %d\n",
98 args->v0.version, args->v0.method, args->v0.head);
99 mthd = args->v0.method;
100 head = args->v0.head;
101 } else
102 return ret;
103
104 if (head < 0 || head >= 2)
105 return -ENXIO;
106
107 switch (mthd) {
108 case NV04_DISP_SCANOUTPOS:
109 return nv04_disp_scanoutpos(root, data, size, head);
110 default:
111 break;
112 }
113
114 return -EINVAL;
115}
116
117static const struct nvkm_object_func
118nv04_disp_root = {
119 .mthd = nv04_disp_mthd,
120 .ntfy = nvkm_disp_ntfy,
121};
122
123static int
124nv04_disp_root_new(struct nvkm_disp *disp, const struct nvkm_oclass *oclass,
125 void *data, u32 size, struct nvkm_object **pobject)
126{
127 struct nv04_disp_root *root;
128
129 if (!(root = kzalloc(sizeof(*root), GFP_KERNEL)))
130 return -ENOMEM;
131 root->disp = disp;
132 *pobject = &root->object;
133
134 nvkm_object_ctor(&nv04_disp_root, oclass, &root->object);
135 return 0;
136}
137
138const struct nvkm_disp_oclass
139nv04_disp_root_oclass = {
140 .base.oclass = NV04_DISP,
141 .base.minver = -1,
142 .base.maxver = -1,
143 .ctor = nv04_disp_root_new,
144};
